From: SDDC_FX3 maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] rx888: drop TUNERSTDBY (0xB8) calls on the HF path

The SDDC_FX3 firmware deliberately removed all R82xx tuner commands
(0xB4 TUNERINIT, 0xB5 TUNERTUNE, 0xB6 SETARGFX3 wIndex 1-4, 0xB8
TUNERSTDBY) — see docs/LICENSE_ANALYSIS.md.  bRequest 0xB8 returns a
clean USB STALL via the firmware's default handler.

ka9q's `rx888_set_hf_mode()` and `rx888_start_rx()` both call
`TUNERSTDBY` unconditionally on the HF path.  The STALL is harmless
in the sense that subsequent commands still work, but it pollutes
the wire and slows init.  Drop both calls; HF receive does not need
them.

Pinned against ka9q-radio commit f78cff9cc8c7fa33ea49aac9176d9263c535a332.
---
 src/rx888.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/rx888.c b/src/rx888.c
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/src/rx888.c
+++ b/src/rx888.c
@@ -940,7 +940,6 @@
 }

 static void rx888_set_hf_mode(struct sdrstate *sdr){
-  command_send(sdr->dev_handle,TUNERSTDBY,0); // Stop Tuner
   // switch to HF Antenna
   usleep(5000);
   sdr->gpios &= ~VHF_EN;
@@ -1000,7 +999,6 @@
   usleep(5000);
   command_send(sdr->dev_handle,STARTFX3,0);
   usleep(5000);
-  command_send(sdr->dev_handle,TUNERSTDBY,0);

   return 0;
 }
